<TITLE> Ashraf bail plea rejected </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 5 (bdnews24.com) - A Dhaka court on Tuesday rejected bail to BNP former former joint secretary general and whip Ashraf Hossain on charges of violating emergency powers rules. Dhaka metropolitan magistrate Faisal Atiq Bin Quader after hearing at 4:30 pm ordered him to jail. Police said they arrested Ashraf in front of Eastern Plaza in Dhanmondi Monday. Later, a general diary was filed with Dhanmondi police charging Ashraf under section 16 (2) of Emergency Powers Rules with making a provocative speech against the government. The GD alleged that whip Ashraf Hossain after being released on bail from Dhaka Central Jail Monday, made the speech to party workers when he reached Eastern Plaza. But Jubo Dal central leader, Humayun Kabir told bdnews24.com Monday: "After Ashraf bhai was released plainclothes policemen took him away in a microbus. The policemen said, 'Sir, get in our car. We need to talk with you.'" Jailer Faruq Ahmed told bdnews24.com Monday: "Former whip Ashraf Hossain was released at 9pm as the High Court has granted him bail." But Faruq said he did not know what happened after Ashraf left the jail. Advocate Shoeb Md Junaid applied for bail on Tuesday on behalf of former whip Ashraf. bdne
